txt.en: 'You there! Do you think you have what it takes to become the best hunter of game in all of Yondershire? Bold words, bold words! Well, I'll be the judge of whether you're worthy of boasting or not.\n\n'How's about I put you to the test? Gamwich can always use more food in the stores for winter. Hunt each of the creatures to be found throughout Yondershire and return to me, and perhaps I will make you an honourary hunter of Gamwich.'
Talk to Gytha Beatbrush in Gamwich
Rare and fearsome creatures for hunting can be found throughout Yondershire.\n\nYou should hunt the rare and fearsome creatures of the Yondershire for Gytha Beatbrush and prove yourself to her.
Gytha Beatbrush can be found in the village of Gamwich.\n\nYou should talk to Gytha Beatbrush in Gamwich.

'You have returned from the hunt! As I am a hobbit of my word, I say you are now an honourary hunter of Gamwich. However...'

Gytha peers at you slyly.

'You are NOT the best hunter of game in Yondershire, for that title belongs to me! If you wish to become my equal, you will have to track down the most elusive and dangerous creatures in this land! Do this, and perhaps we will stand on equal footing: the finest game hunters in Yondershire. I will at least be impressed.'
Gytha Beatbrush, the master hunter of Gamwich wonders if you have what it takes to be a master of the hunt!
Creatures for hunting can be found throughout Yondershire.\n\nYou should hunt the creatures of the Yondershire for Gytha Beatbrush and prove yourself to her.
Gytha Beatbrush can be found in the village of Gamwich.\n\nYou should talk to Gytha Beatbrush in Gamwich.

'Your hunt of those elusive and fearsome creatures was successful? I am impressed! I did not really expect you to succeed, but I am pleased that you have. Perhaps we are equals in the hunt after all, and even better: the villages of Yondershire are made safer by your efforts, which is the most important thing. Well done!'
Talk to Gytha Beatbrush in Gamwich
